Description: Changes of landscape diversity and structure can be detected
    soon if relying on landscape class combinations and analysing patterns
    at multiple scales. 'LandComp' provides such an opportunity, based on
    Juhász-Nagy's functions. Functions can handle multilayered data.
    Requirements of the input: binary data contained by a regular square
    or hexagonal grid, and the grid should have projected coordinates.
    Juhász-Nagy P (1976) "Spatial dependence of plant populations. Part 1.
    Equivalence analysis (An outline of new model)"
    <https:ricottalab.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/juhasz-nagy-1976.pdf>
    Juhász-Nagy P (1984) "Spatial dependence of plant population. 2. A
    family of new models"
    <https:ricottalab.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/juhasz-nagy-1984b.pdf>
    Juhász-Nagy P (1993) "Notes on compositional diversity"
    <doi:10.1007/BF00008852>
    Juhász-Nagy P, Podani J (1983) "Information theory methods for the
    study of spatial processes and succession" <doi:10.1007/BF00129432>
